The moving paracord will be orange paracord while the black paracord only act as a core
Place the right paracord beneath the black paracord but on top of the left paracord. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/fa/Make-a-Paracord-550-Bracelet-Without-Buckle-%28Cobra-Stich-Followed-by-King-Cobra%29-Step-5Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Paracord-550-Bracelet-Without-Buckle-%28Cobra-Stich-Followed-by-King-Cobra%29-Step-5Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/f/fa/Make-a-Paracord-550-Bracelet-Without-Buckle-%28Cobra-Stich-Followed-by-King-Cobra%29-Step-5Bullet2.jpg/aid4336361-v4-728px-Make-a-Paracord-550-Bracelet-Without-Buckle-%28Cobra-Stich-Followed-by-King-Cobra%29-Step-5Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
